# Financial Risk Solvency MTV Net Aggregate Amount

## identifier
de5597

## type
float

## definition
Report the Minimum Termination Value (MTV) as determined by the prudential standards, net of reinsurance. MTV is the amount that a life insurer is obliged to pay to policyholders if they decided to voluntarily terminate their policies at the relevant date. The obligation might be contractual, statutory or a result of past practice. Calculated as the greater of: 
a) the lowest Termination Value that the reporting party is obliged to pay; and 
b) the amount calculated in accordance with the Surrender Value Standard.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=credit
- name=FinancialRisk.Solvency.MTVNetAggregate.Amount
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.05
- period=instant
